OL,6,FToad rescuers in say they have helped
OL,7,Fthe highest number of amphibians to
OL,8,Fsafely cross the road in 14 years.
OL,10,FMore than 50 volunteers from the
OL,11,FCharlcombe Toad Rescue Group helped
OL,12,F3,177 amphibians across a half-mile
OL,13,Fstretch of Charlcombe Lane during the
OL,14,F2024 migration season.
OL,16,FThe 2024 patrol saw the second highest
OL,17,Fnumber of amphibians recorded since
OL,18,Fthe road was first closed to traffic
OL,19,Fduring the migration season in 2003.
