OL,6,FCharlcombe Lane is closed annually for
OL,7,Fsix weeks in February and March as
OL,8,Fvolunteers patrol every night from
OL,9,Fdusk to help common toads, common
OL,10,Ffrogs and newts on their journey to
OL,11,Ftheir breeding lake.
OL,13,FAcross the six weeks, the 52
OL,14,Fvolunteers spent more than 600 hours
OL,15,Fwalking slowly up and down the road,
OL,16,Farmed with torches and buckets.
OL,18,FToads, frogs and newts are carefully
OL,19,Fpicked up and carried safely to drop-
OL,20,Foff points to help them on their
OL,21,Fjourney towards the lake.
